# Product Marketing Docs

The `product-marketing/` folder (symlinked from an external repo) contains marketing-level documentation used by the FE illustration project for translation and content work. These are NOT technical docs — no DB schemas, function names, or API endpoints.

## Folder Structure

```
product-marketing/
├── Product/
│   ├── PRODUCT_OVERVIEW.md          — Module relationships, platform positioning
│   ├── LOYALTY_FEATURES.md          — Loyalty feature descriptions
│   ├── MARKETING_AUTOMATION_FEATURES.md — AMP / automation feature descriptions
│   └── CUSTOMER_SERVICE_FEATURES.md — CS feature descriptions
└── Translation/
    ├── TRANSLATION_PHILOSOPHY.md    — Universal translation rules
    ├── ENGLISH_CONTEXT.md           — English vocabulary + writing conventions
    ├── JAPAN_CONTEXT.md             — Japanese market context
    ├── TAIWAN_CONTEXT.md            — Taiwanese market context
    └── THAILAND_CONTEXT.md          — Thai market context
```

## When to Update

Only after **major** changes visible to customers:

| Trigger | Example | Update? |
|---|---|---|
| Brand-new feature or sub-feature | New mission type, new channel, new CS action | Yes |
| Feature renamed or core behavior fundamentally changed | "Workflows" → "Automation Rules" | Yes |
| New module or product line added | A fourth module | Yes |
| New market-facing term introduced | Term that would appear in UI copy | Yes |
| Bugfix | Fix wallet balance calculation | No |
| Performance improvement | Speed up tier evaluation | No |
| Internal refactor | Rename DB function, restructure code | No |
| API change with no customer-visible effect | Change BFF response shape | No |
| Incremental enhancement to existing feature | Add a filter option to an existing list | No |

## Domain → Doc Mapping

| Domain | Product-Marketing Doc |
|---|---|
| Missions, Rewards, Currency, Tier, Tag/Persona, Referral, Forms, Checkin, Stored Value Card, Store, Activity/Earning, Purchase | `Product/LOYALTY_FEATURES.md` |
| AMP Workflows, AMP AI Agent | `Product/MARKETING_AUTOMATION_FEATURES.md` |
| CS Conversations, Knowledge Base, Procedures, Channels, Customers | `Product/CUSTOMER_SERVICE_FEATURES.md` |
| New module or cross-module relationship change | `Product/PRODUCT_OVERVIEW.md` |

## How to Write

1. **Marketing level only.** What does this do for the brand or their customers? Not how it's implemented.
2. **No technical details.** No function names, table names, API endpoints, DB schemas.
3. **Outcome-first.** "Automatically reward customers when they reach a spending milestone" — not "trigger_milestone_reward fires when purchase_total exceeds tier threshold."
4. **Match the existing tone.** Read the doc you're updating before writing. Follow its structure and voice.

## Translation Handling

If a new domain term is introduced in English:
1. Add it to the vocabulary table in `Translation/ENGLISH_CONTEXT.md`
2. Flag JP/TW/TH docs as needing a translation entry — add a comment or note at the top of each affected file
3. Do NOT guess translations — only add the English source term

